#IWCPilot #IWCON

node.text:
Congratulations to brand ambassador @LewisHamilton on being awarded the Laureus Athlete Advocate of the Year Award at the 22nd edition of the Laureus World Sports Awards.
“A huge thank you to the Laureus World Sports Academy for presenting me with this incredible Award. This past year has been incredibly difficult for so many, but it has also been heartening to see the power of our collective voices spark new conversations and change. The global rising to address the longstanding issue of systemic racism and inequality in our society has been monumental, but we must continue to fight. We must all see ourselves as responsible for making positive change in our world, and hold ourselves accountable, so that the promises of last year turn in to action. I truly believe that together, we will get there, and so I stand with you as we push forwards.” #IWCLaureus #LewisHamilton

node.title: LEWIS HAMILTON HONOURED FOR ADVOCACY WORK AT #LAUREUS21

@paulripke is a German photographer who lives in Newport Beach, California. Over the past years he worked in Formula1 as the photographer of the @mercedesamgf1 team.

node.text:
Ever sleek, The Big Pilot's Watch (Ref. IW501001) comes in a 46-millimetre case, which is water-resistant to 6 bar, encloses a soft-iron inner case that protects the movement against magnetic fields. The watch also features a striking conical crown. The legendary Junkers JU-52 plane is engraved on the case back. 
#IWCON #IWCPilot

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by IWC Schaffhausen on July 12, 2021. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text:
The highly efficient Calibre 52's winding system is a refined version of the 50000-calibre family with a bidirectional Pellaton pawl-winding system. Two barrels provide an impressive 7 days’ power reserve. The winding pawls and the automatic wheel are made of black ceramic while the rotor bearing is made of white ceramic. 
#IWCON #IWCPilot
